          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>417</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">Removable Singularity</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>Removable Singularity.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Removable Singularity">Removable Singularity</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>25</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>This is <fr:strong>not true</fr:strong> for real functions</fr:p>
            <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:anchor>411</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">Removable Singularity Theorem</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>Removable Singularity Theorem.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Removable Singularity Theorem">Removable Singularity Theorem</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>5</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>25</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p><fr:strong>Theorem</fr:strong>: Suppose that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is continuous on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B_r(z_0)]]></fr:tex> and <fr:link type="local" href="holomorphic.xml" addr="holomorphic" title="Holomorphic">holomorphic</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B_r(z_0) \setminus  \{z_0\}]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link type="local" href="holomorphic.xml" addr="holomorphic" title="Holomorphic">holomorphic</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B_r(z_0)]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
              <fr:backmatter />
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:p>The same conclusion of the theorem holds if we extend:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B_r(z_0)]]></fr:tex> to an open set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>The single point <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ \{z_0\} ]]></fr:tex> to a line segment parallel to the axes.</fr:li></fr:ul>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z_0]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:link type="external" href="isolated%20singularity">isolated singularity</fr:link> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>. If there exists a <fr:link type="local" href="holomorphic.xml" addr="holomorphic" title="Holomorphic">holomorphic</fr:link> extension of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B_r(z_0)]]></fr:tex> then the singularity is <fr:strong>removable</fr:strong></fr:p>
            <fr:p><fr:strong>N.B.</fr:strong> Not all singularities are removable, for example <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f(z) = \frac {1}{z}]]></fr:tex> has a non-removable singularity at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z_0 = 0]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Notice that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ \not \exists  \lim _{z \to  0} f(z) ]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
            <fr:p>Similarly for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f(z) = \frac {1}{{(z-z_0)}^n}]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
            <fr:p>In contrast, the function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f(z) = \frac {sinz}{z}]]></fr:tex> has a removable singularity at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z_0 = 0]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Indeed <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ \lim _{z \to  0} \frac {sinz}{z} = 1 ]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
